    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWith nvim 0.10, nvim sends excessive (endless) amount of `grid_cursor_goto` and `flush` messages when the popupmenu is open (with ext_popupmenu).\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. use a GUI that as externalized popupmenu implemented and enabled (requires ext_popupmenu)\r\n2. get your nvim to a state that it shows the popupmenu\r\n3. observe the endless cursor goto and flush events\r\n\r\nI pushed a branch to gnvim to make testing easier: https://github.com/vhakulinen/gnvim/tree/debug/excessive-cursor-goto (https://github.com/vhakulinen/gnvim/tree/e8b72c3c543e0ed953579fbb8175cb59f2ea6039 for exact commit).\r\n\r\nIf you have all the requirements installed on your system (i.e. latest gtk4) you can just run `cargo run --bin gnvim -- --nvim-args \"-u NONE\"` to test with a plain nvim. You can also use flatpak (see the README instructions). The default `make run` uses flatpak, and that branch has the nvim args adjusted.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNot sending unnecessary cursor goto events.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nPop!_OS 22.04 LTS\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ngnvim\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from source",
