            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It seems that resetting [these](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/e778e0116198470ba037b9426f4ff7fa5cb7f880#diff-53486731970573492a91272bd9c6b764402a36b087c2ad24fee49fd09fa1cbd3L1111-L1113) variables before flushing the ext UI to avoid recursiveness there, in turn results in recursive `showmode()`'s because they may be set to `true` again by the function itself. I guess we set them to false at the start **and** end of `showmode()`.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, partly revert that change and just add a recursion guard to `showmode()`. I think that would be sufficient as well and better conveys the intention than moving some global variable access.",
